                        **** PRE BRAMS ***
                        * HOW TO INSTALL *
                        ******************

Please, if You will use mpich3 refer to BRAMS_INSTALL_COMPLETE_MANUAL.pdf
to install it.

If You have the items 1 to 5 installed in Your OS goto to item 6.

1. Install grib2:
------------------

a)Create a install directory (in this case: ~/install), get the file:

mkdir ~/install
cd ~/install
wget https://www.ftp.cpc.ncep.noaa.gov/wd51we/wgrib2/wgrib2.tgz
tar -zxvf wgrib2.tgz
cd grib2

b) Using your editor edit the makefile and change the values:

USE_NETCDF3=0     
USE_NETCDF4=0     
USE_REGEX=1     
USE_TIGGE=1     
USE_MYSQL=0     
USE_IPOLATES=3     
USE_SPECTRAL=0     
USE_UDF=0     
USE_OPENMP=0     
USE_PROJ4=0     
USE_WMO_VALIDATION=0     
DISABLE_TIMEZONE=0     
MAKE_FTN_API=1     
DISABLE_ALARM=0     
USE_G2CLIB=0     
USE_PNG=0     
USE_JASPER=0     
USE_AEC=0

c) Make the files (in this case the compilers are gfortran/gcc, You can try others):

make CC=gcc FC=gfortran
make CC=gcc FC=gfortran lib
cd ..
sudo mv grib2 /opt

OBS: In this case the files are moved to /opt folder. You can choose other one! The sudo may be not used.

d) Check if libraries and modules was compiled:

ls /opt/grib2/lib
libgeo.a  libip2_d.a  libwgrib2.a  libwgrib2_api.a  libwgrib2x.a  makefile  wgrib2api.mod  wgrib2lowapi.mod



2. Install ZLIB
---------------

If You have Zlib installed You can goto to next item.
(in this case the compilers are gcc, You can try others):

a) Goto install folder and get the file

cd ~/install
wget https://www.zlib.net/zlib-1.2.11.tar.xz

b) Unpack the file:

xz -d zlib-1.2.11.tar.xz
tar -xvf zlib-1.2.11.tar

c) Goto to floder created and compile:

cd zlib-1.2.11
CC=gcc ./configure --prefix=/opt/zlib
make
sudo make install

OBS: In this case the files are installed in /opt folder. You can choose other one! 
     In case of use home folder sudo may be not used.



3. Install HDF5:
-----------------

a) In your browser go to https://www.hdfgroup.org/downloads/hdf5/source-code/ and download the newest source code 
   to install folder (or Download Folder) You create previously. (In example the version is hdf5-1.10.6.tar.bz2)

b) Go to folder, Unpack and compile HDF5:

cd ~/install
mv ~/Downloads/hdf5-1.10.6.tar.bz2 .
bunzip2 hdf5-1.10.6.tar.bz2
tar -xvf hdf5-1.10.6.tar
cd hdf5-1.10.6.tar.bz2
./configure --prefix=/opt/hdf5 CC=/opt/mpich3/bin/mpicc FC=/opt/mpich3/bin/mpif90 --with-zlib=/opt/zlib --enable-parallel --enable-fortran
make
sudo make install

OBS: 1.In this case the files are installed in /opt folder. You can choose other one! 
       In case of use home folder sudo may be not used.
     2.Please, see that --with-zlib must use the zlib installed previsously.
     3.You can use gcc/gfortran compiler instead mpich3 



4. Install NetCDF C:
--------------------
a) In your browser go to https://www.unidata.ucar.edu/downloads/netcdf/ and download the newest source code 
   to install folder (or Download Folder) You create previously. (In example the version is netcdf-c-4.7.3.tar.gz)

b) Go to folder, unpack and compile:

cd ~/install
mv ~/Downloads/netcdf-c-4.7.3.tar.gz .
tar -xzvf netcdf-c-4.7.3.tar.gz
cd netcdf-c-4.7.3
./configure --prefix=/opt/netcdfc FC=/opt/mpich3/bin/mpif90 CC=/opt/mpich3/bin/mpicc LT_SYS_LIBRARY_PATH=/opt/hdf5/lib CFLAGS='-I/opt/hdf5/include' LIBS='-L/opt/hdf5/lib'
make
sudo make install

OBS: 1.In this case the files are installed in /opt folder. You can choose other one! 
       In case of use home folder sudo may be not used.
     2.You can use gcc/gfortran compilers or others compilers instead mpich3
     3.POint the LIBRARY, Include and LIBS to HDF5 path installed previously 



5. Install NetCDF Fortran:
--------------------------

a) In your browser go to https://www.unidata.ucar.edu/downloads/netcdf/ and download the newest source code 
   to install folder (or Download Folder) You create previously. (In example the version is netcdf-fortran-4.5.2.tar.gz)

b) Go to folder, unpack and compile:

cd ~/install
mv ~/Downloads/netcdf-fortran-4.5.2.tar.gz .
tar -xzvf netcdf-fortran-4.5.2.tar.gz
cd netcdf-fortran-4.5.2
export LD_LIBRARY_PATH=/opt/netcdfc/lib:/opt/hdf5/lib:$LD_LIBRARY_PATH
export CC=/opt/mpich3/bin/mpicc
export FC=/opt/mpich3/bin/mpif90
export CPPFLAGS="-I/opt/netcdfc/include -I/opt/hdf5/include"
export LDFLAGS="-L/opt/netcdfc/lib -L/opt/hdf5/lib"
./configure --prefix=/opt/netcdff
make
sudo make install

OBS: 1.In this case the files are installed in /opt folder. You can choose other one! 
       In case of use home folder sudo may be not used.
     2.You can use gcc/gfortran compilers or others compilers instead mpich3
       use the same compiler You choose ever!
     3.Point the LIBRARY, Include and LIBS to HDF5 path installed previously 
     4.Point the LIBRARY, Include and LIBS to NetCDF C path installed previously 


6. Install PRE-BRAMS:
---------------------

a) Go to PRE-BRAMS build directory 

cd ~/BRAMS-5.5/auxProgs/PRE-BRAMS/build

b) Edit the file paths.mk and change the lines accordingly:

CHEM_MECH=RELACS_TUV
GRIB2_PATH=/opt/grib2/
NETCDFC_PATH=/opt/netcdfc
NETCDFF_PATH=/opt/netcdff

c) There are just one include.mk.XXX file, for gnu compiler (gcc/gfortran). 
   where XXX is the compiler environment (GNU, etc)
   If You will use another one please, copy it for a new and edit the lines:

FC           =gfortran
FC_OPTS      = -DUSEPARALELL=$(USEPARALELL) -DUSEGRIB=$(USEGRIB) -ffree-form -ffree-line-length-none
FLOADER      =gfortran

  **** Change to compiler You want and save it. If compiler id ifort, include.mk.intel e.g.:

FC           =ifort
FC_OPTS      = -DUSEPARALELL=$(USEPARALELL) -DUSEGRIB=$(USEGRIB)
FLOADER      =ifort

d) Compile the PRE:

make OPT=gnu

OBS: 1. All defined path must be compliance with previously installed libraries.
     2. All the libraries must use the same compiler You choose.
     3. The make above is for include.mk.gnu



7. Get data to run:
-------------------

For run the PRE you need 2 sets of files, CAMS climatology files and GRIB2 GFS files.

a) create a data folder to put all datafiles and goto it:

mkdir ~/data
cd ~/data

a) Get the cams climatology on: http://ftp.cptec.inpe.br/pesquisa/bramsrd/DATA_CAMS/
The files have the format: MMM-CAMS-EC-2010-2019-AMS.nc where MMM are the month (JAN,FEB,...)

wget http://ftp.cptec.inpe.br/pesquisa/bramsrd/DATA_CAMS/SEP-CAMS-EC-2010-2019-AMS.nc

b) Get the GFS data from nomads on https://nomads.ncep.noaa.gov/pub/data/nccf/com/gfs/prod/gfs.YYYYMMDD/HH/gfs.t00z.pgrb2.0p25.fPPP where:

YYYY - Year with 4 digits
MM - MOnth with 2 digits
DD - Day with 2 digits
HH - Hour (00,06,12 or 18) of run
PPP - Time for analysis (from 000 until 384)

get the data You have interest. E.g. If You want to generate data for 24h, 6/6 hours  begining 01Sep2020:

wget https://nomads.ncep.noaa.gov/pub/data/nccf/com/gfs/prod/gfs.20200901/00/gfs.t00z.pgrb2.0p25.f000 -O gfs.t00z.pgrb2.0p25.f000.2020090100.grib2
wget https://nomads.ncep.noaa.gov/pub/data/nccf/com/gfs/prod/gfs.20200901/00/gfs.t00z.pgrb2.0p25.f006 -O gfs.t00z.pgrb2.0p25.f002.2020090100.grib2
wget https://nomads.ncep.noaa.gov/pub/data/nccf/com/gfs/prod/gfs.20200901/00/gfs.t00z.pgrb2.0p25.f012 -O gfs.t00z.pgrb2.0p25.f012.2020090100.grib2
wget https://nomads.ncep.noaa.gov/pub/data/nccf/com/gfs/prod/gfs.20200901/00/gfs.t00z.pgrb2.0p25.f018 -O gfs.t00z.pgrb2.0p25.f018.2020090100.grib2
wget https://nomads.ncep.noaa.gov/pub/data/nccf/com/gfs/prod/gfs.20200901/00/gfs.t00z.pgrb2.0p25.f024 -O gfs.t00z.pgrb2.0p25.f024.2020090100.grib2

OBS: 1. The name of file from NOMADS dont have the date of run. Put a suffix in date to inform it, above using ".2020090100.grib2"
     2. You can choose other data folder You want.
     3. You must Download Cams CLimatology just once. Save it for use in future.
     4. If your run pass from one month to other(s) You must download all cams climatology months You need.



8. Edit the namelist for PRE:
-----------------------------

a) Go to bin folder:

 cd ~/BRAMS-5.5/auxProgs/PRE-BRAMS/bin

b) Edit Namelist file 'pre.nml' to correct run:


init_year  = 2020,
init_month = 09,
init_day   = 01,
init_hour  = 0,
final_year = 2020,
final_month= 09,
final_day =  02,
final_hour = 0,
...
step  = 6, !Timestep in hours
...
atmos_prefix ='gfs.t00z.pgrb2.0p25.f',
atmos_sufix  ='.2020090100.grib2',
atmos_idir   ='~/dados/',
...
chem_idir  = '~/dados/',
chem1_prefix ='',
chem1_sufix  ='-CAMS-EC-2010-2019-AMS',
...
out_prefix = 'IC',
out_sufix  = '',
out_dir    = '~/bin/datain/GRADS/',

OBS: 1. The example above is for the date of 01Sep2020 with 24h simulation.
     2. The output directory is set to put the initial conditions in your BRAMS run folder.


9. Run the PRE:
---------------

a) just run the executable:

./PREP_1.0


